\p{I wish to have some notes about raycasting implicit surfaces. Particularly, I wish to figure out why [this shadertoy code](https://www.shadertoy.com/view/l3BSRG) ( my adapted version: [[uts-000J]] ) works decently well for implicit surfaces with singularities but not other algorithms, e.g. [[uts-000K]].
}

\p{This is also an experiment to see how well the following 4 mix together in Forester:
\ul{
  \li{formal math notes of the concepts and formulas}
  \li{illustrative diagrams in TikZ}
  \li{psuedocode of the algorithms, then syntax highlighted acutal shade code}
  \li{the rendered GL canvas}
}
}

\p{See [[uts-000G]] and [[uts-000H]] for some links as references.
